  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-22 08:58 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] Late Pinned Episodes Age Into Noisier Conviction, Not Clean Decay\n\n**Task:** Compare 08h against 07h inside the same long pinned episode to see whether later excluded hours become more tradable, stay stable, or decay in a useful way.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and PM remains out of active hours.\n- Both hours stayed structurally identical:\n  - **07h:** **60/60** windows in `(0.505, 0.495)`\n  - **08h:** **49/49** windows in `(0.505, 0.495)`\n- But the conviction mix changed:\n  - **07h**\n    - `|bias| >= 45`: **32** (**53.3%**)\n    - `|bias| >= 55`: **9** (**15.0%**)\n    - `<35`: **16** (**26.7%**)\n    - max bias: **69.8**\n  - **08h**\n    - `|bias| >= 45`: **20** (**40.8%**)\n    - `|bias| >= 55`: **10** (**20.4%**)\n    - `<35`: **19** (**38.8%**)\n    - max bias: **68.5**\n- Wrote new research artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v7s-pinned-episode-aging.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is not a clean \u201clater hours simply weaken\u201d result. 08h stayed perfectly pinned, lost a meaningful chunk of mid-to-high conviction density at `45+`, and picked up more low-conviction drift under `35`, but it still produced slightly more `55+` spikes than 07h. So the right model is not smooth decay. It is **aging with noisier conviction distribution** inside the same unchanged structure.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep **08h excluded**.\n- Treat later stages of pinned episodes as **noisier and less reliably tradable**, even when the structural regime stays unchanged.\n- Preserve the rule that persistent excluded structure does not become a live candidate just because it lasts longer.\n\n**Next:** On the next P2 heartbeat, compare the full pinned-episode conviction profile against live-hour distributions to quantify how far these long excluded episodes still sit from deployable active-hour quality.\n\n